Class GridForceRestartDelegateServlet

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.servlet.GenericServlet
      • javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
        • org.openqa.grid.web.servlet.RegistryBasedServlet
          • com.paypal.selion.grid.servlets.GridForceRestartDelegateServlet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig

    public class GridForceRestartDelegateServlet
extends org.openqa.grid.web.servlet.RegistryBasedServlet
    This RegistryBasedServlet based servlet is responsible for sending restart requests to all the registered nodes.

    This requires the hub to also have LoginServlet available. Furthermore, only nodes which use SeLionRemoteProxy and NodeForceRestartServlet or implement support for the HTTP request /extra/NodeForceRestartServlet are compatible.

    If there isn't a process, such as SeLion's Grid with continuousRestart on, monitoring and restarting the node on exit(), the node will be shutdown but not restarted.
    See Also:
